  "elapsed_s": 10.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there were many select-- many selections during the stay.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was-- I was in Birkenau for approximately four weeks.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in the four weeks, selection is-- there were a number of selections, because a number of transports left Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So every time there was a selection, new people came, newer transports came.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] We-- the selections we were worried about was the selections when they picked up people who looked weak.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The selection-- oh, the other selections we worried about when we had to go to-- for inspection [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] to the-- to the-- to the doctors.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they looked at our-- our body-- take a closer look at our body, and which maybe wouldn't have been a-- you couldn't have seen it from outside.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I think mainly the main reason was of these-- of these so-called examinations, which was only people walking through between two tables to spot any sort of illness maybe, probably cont-- contagious in this-- which they didn't want.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And there were a number of people-- a number of people didn't return to the-- to the barracks after these inspections.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But one day we knew when we were sent on a transport [? everyone ?] finishes up.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "One thing everybody knew is anything was better than staying in Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because the longer one stayed in Birkenau, the chances were getting slimmer and slimmer of getting out of Birkenau alive because the food was absolutely bare necessity.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The circumstances as such, which I'm sure many hundreds of people, thousands of people described before me, were not such that one would have wanted to stay in Birkenau, but mostly because of the-- of the fear of, of the gas chambers and mostly the fear of the selections.",
      "word_count": 49
    }
  ],
